The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, March 08, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, March 7: The countrys foreign exchange reserves surged by $685 million to touch $108.36 billion following fresh inflows and revaluation of the US currency vis--vis other currencies for the week ended February 27, according to the Reserve Bank Of Indias weekly statistical bulletin. The foreign currency assets also saw a similar increase to touch $104.06 billion, it said.																								 Mumbai, March 7: IDFC Asset Management Company will invest around Rs 300 crore from its Rs 1,000-crore India Development Fund. Its first disbursal of Rs 100 crore is likely to be made next week.																								 Mumbai, March 7: Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd (MTNL) has waived a security deposit of Rs 1,000 for its lease- line circuit connectivity for corporate and individual customers, effective March 1. 																								 Mumbai, March 7: Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) will increase its network of auto LPG dispensing stations by setting up 11 more units by June. These will include four in Calcutta, two in Chennai and one each in Mumbai and Kanpur at a cost of Rs 4.4 crore, director (marketing) N. G. Kannan said.																								 Mumbai, March 7: Radico Khaitan has raised $10 million through external commercial borrowings to fund its business growth plans and repay existing loans.
